London Abram vivian
Sr. my last to you was on the 7: curit, sence non from yyou so please tobe
referred tothe same principally in providing a 100: bayes more, besides my formar
order: thomas smith is well arrived, butt them on his board will not serve my turne
for there beeng more bespoaken already, so if they be good they will sell well
a rither then faile lett the first bale that might be ready att Hull be shipt
for Rotterdam to my order provided the ship for that please shoul despeert
sooner then that for oftend: on which I do depend: yd acctt. are ready & till
follow pr next whilst intrim & do much wonder to have not yd advise
whom to draw up on for yeasterday I was forceed to barrow mony to pay billon the
21 which is within must be payd £200: more so delay not to advise mee the
need full, if you knew how cheap the laces are now you would come over & provid
